# matter.word — the matter type registry + what a matter IS.
# The world strand of seed/materials/matter; the host classify/fold/CAS stay.

# The registered types. Each: the content it accepts, the ops it carries,
# and any classification claims it stakes. "It" refers to the type just named
# (rule 19: a kind stays lowercase; only beings and I / I are capitalized).
A generic is a matter type.
It accepts text or no content.
It carries set-matter and end-matter.

A file is a matter type.
It accepts binary or text content.
It carries set-matter, end-matter, and purge-content.

A model is a matter type.
It accepts binary content.
It carries set-matter, end-matter, and purge-content.
It claims a glb or gltf extension.

A source is a matter type.
It accepts text, binary, or no content.
It carries create-matter, set-matter, end-matter, and rename-matter.

# What a matter is (the structure every matter carries).
A matter has an owner, the being that created it.
A matter has a type, a registered name.
A matter has content, a shape matching its type.
A matter has qualities, the properties it carries.
A matter has a position in its space.
